ia gubernatorial election, 2018|Governor of California]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c-AvQFoKm5w|title=Wildstar Endorses Larry Sharpe For Governor|date=September 19, 2017|accessdate=November 8, 2017}}</ref>\n;Television and radio personalities\n* [[Glenn Beck]], conservative political commentator and radio host at [[TheBlaze]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://omny.fm/shows/the-glenn-beck-program/best-of-the-program-with-larry-sharpe-10-1-18|title=Best of the Program with Larry Sharpe \u2013 10/1/18 \u2013 Glenn Beck \u2013 Omny.fm|website=Omny.fm|accessdate=October 4, 2018}}</ref>\n* Shannon Joy, [[WYSL]] radio host<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/shannon.wysl/posts/1061478290673151|title=Shannon Joy|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=July 17, 2018}}{{Primary source inline|date=August 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Joanne Nosuchinsky]], 2013 [[Miss USA 2013|Miss New York USA]] and co-host of Mornin'!!! with Bill Schulz<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/JoNosuchinsky/status/1057297224672178178|title=Joanne Nosuchinsky on Twitter|publisher=Twitter|accessdate=November 8, 2018}}{{Primary source inline|date=August 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Evan Roberts (radio personality)|Evan Roberts]], sports radio talk personality and co-host of ''[[Joe & Evan]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/EvanRobertsWFAN/status/1058835213638397953|title=Evan Roberts on Twitter|publisher=Twitter|accessdate=November 8, 2018}}{{Primary source inline|date=August 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Joe Rogan]], comedian, [[mixed martial arts]] [[color commentator]], [[podcast]] host, and businessman<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nSmggQZno6w|title=Joe Rogan Experience #1167 \u2013 Larry Sharpe|date=September 5, 2018|accessdate=November 8, 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n* [[Dave Rubin]], political commentator and talk show host, creator and host of [[The Rubin Report]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RTj8ZoCiM4E|title=A Libertarian Running for Governor of New York (Larry Sharpe Full Interview)|date=July 13, 2018|accessdate=November 8, 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n* [[Bill Schulz]], journalist, television personality and host of Mornin'!!! with Bill Schulz<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/BillSchulz/status/1057068834316828672|title=Bill Schulz on Twitter|publisher=Twitter|accessdate=November 8, 2018}}{{Primary source inline|date=August 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Katherine Timpf]], comedian, reporter and [[Fox News]] television personality<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bESZo3jdz54|title=Gutfeld: Why election stress only damages the left|date=November 3, 2018|accessdate=November 8, 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n;Commentators, writers, and columnists\n* Bob Confer, columnist for the [[Lockport Union-Sun & Journal]] and the [[Niagara Gazette]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.niagara-gazette.com/opinion/confer-the-sharpest-candidate-for-governor/article_5b3a69c8-de0f-532a-8ab1-a4acad7d6987.html|title=CONFER: The sharpest candidate for governor|author=Confer, Bob|date=September 19, 2018|accessdate=September 23, 2018|newspaper=[[Niagara Gazette]]}}</ref>\n* Jeremy Frankel, writer for [[The Daily Wire]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/FrankelJeremy/status/1040578662456811521|title=Jeremy \"Spartacus\" Frankel on Twitter|publisher=Twitter|accessdate=October 4, 2018}}{{Primary source inline|date=August 2019}}</ref>\n* [[John Stossel]], author, journalist and libertarian news commentator<ref>{{cite web|url=https://triblive.com/opinion/featuredcommentary/14242568-74/john-stossel-libertarian-has-sharp-ideas-for-ny|title=John Stossel: Libertarian has sharp ideas for NY|date=November 2, 2018|accessdate=November 2, 2018|work=Trib Live|author=Stossel, John}}</ref>\n* [[Matt Welch]], journalist at [[Reason (magazine)|''Reason'']]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MattWelch/status/1059894512468803585|title=Matt Welch on Twitter|publisher=Twitter|accessdate=November 8, 2018}}{{Primary source inline|date=August 2019}}</ref>\n;Musicians and artists\n* [[Gerald Walker]], hip-hop musician<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/WalkWithGerald/status/1050916223607816192|title=Gerald Walker on Twitter|publisher=Twitter|accessdate=November 8, 2018}}{{Primary source inline|date=August 2019}}</ref>\n;Athletes and sports figures\n* [[Aron Price]], professional golfer<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/aronpricePGA/status/1046368355479945217|title=Aron Price on Twitter|publisher=Twitter|accessdate=October 4, 2018}}{{Primary source inline|date=August 2019}}</ref>\n;Social and political activists\n* Matthew Kolken, immigration lawyer and elected member of the [[American Immigration Lawyers Association|AILA]] board of directors<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/mkolken/status/1045350423891251201|title=Matthew Kolken on Twitter|publisher=Twitter|accessdate=October 4, 2018}}{{Primary source inline|date=August 2019}}</ref>\n;Organizations\n* 71Republic<ref>{{cite web|url=https://71republic.com/2018/06/03/dear-new-york-elect-larry-sharpe/|title=Dear New York: Elect Larry Sharpe \u2013 71 Republic|date=June 3, 2018|website=71republic.com|accessdate=July 17, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613184130/https://71republic.com/2018/06/03/dear-new-york-elect-larry-sharpe/|archive-date=June 13, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* Libertarian Youth Caucus<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/LYCaucus/posts/2251222821764174?__xts__%5B0%5D=68.ARDi628ETLyOpTcW4kIb0HznfDKTd6vfu2rOq6EnQ1AzhYUkVn8o_4ffrC2caUDWW-zxoihe0HZtp3wslnB4sZ7tVjC8D-SMPWspcVbyapkdUNIi1ad6Nl1DXHCABHLfcC00l2fD0r4-9ZxTicmdLYbEFh74lUAHRJiILN-OHnOdX1SDBkQoTg&__tn__=C-R|title=Libertarian Youth Caucus|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=November 8, 2018}}{{Primary source inline|date=August 2019}}</ref>\n* Marijuana Reform Party of New York state<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mailchi.mp/cannabis4ny.org/apologies-to-our-republican-libertarian-and-independent-supporters|title=Apologies to Our Republican, Libertarian and Independent Supporters|website=Mailchi.mp|accessdate=July 17, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Monroe County, New York|Monroe County]] Libertarian Party<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/MonroeCountyLibertarianParty/posts/1857286200949757|title=Monroe County Libertarian Party|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=October 4, 2018}}{{Primary source inline|date=August 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Onondaga County, New York|Onondaga County]] Libertarian Party<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lpnewyork.org/2018/04/10/onondaga-lp-chapter-endorses-candidates-elects-officers/|title=Onondaga LP Chapter Endorses Candidates, Elects Officers|author=Kolstee, Andrew|date=April 10, 2018|accessdate=April 13, 2018|work=Libertarian Party of New York|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180414010358/https://lpnewyork.org/2018/04/10/onondaga-lp-chapter-endorses-candidates-elects-officers/|archive-date=April 14, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Otsego County, New York|Otsego County]] Libertarian Party<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/LP_OtsegoCounty/status/1046149194254290946|title=OtsegoCountyLibertarians on Twitter|publisher=Twitter|accessdate=October 4, 2018}}{{Primary source inline|date=August 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n====Post-2018 campaign activities====\nFollowing the 2018 election, Sharpe continued speaking tours across New York State.<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/pg/Sharpe4Gov/events/ Larry Sharpe, Libertarian - Events]</ref> In 2019, he launched ''The Sharpe Way'', an [[Webcast|online talk show]].<ref>[https://sharpeway.com/ The Sharpe Way]</ref>\n\n===2020 vice presidential campaign===\nOn April 13, 2020 it was announced that Sharpe would again seek the Libertarian Party's nomination for Vice President, as the running mate of 2012 Libertarian vice-presidential nominee [[James P. Gray|Judge Jim Gray]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://reason.com/2020/04/13/judge-jim-gray-to-seek-libertarian-presidential-nomination/|title=Judge Jim Gray To Seek Libertarian Presidential Nomination|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 13, 2020|work=[[Reason (magazine)|Reason]]|author=Welch, Matt}}</ref>\n\n==Political positions==\nSharpe supports reducing regulations such as [[occupational licensing]] as well as legalizing marijuana and decriminalizing other drugs.<ref name=\"WAER\">{{cite web|authors=Willis, Scott, Liam McMonagle, and Chris Bolt|url=http://waer.org/post/libertarian-candidate-gov-i-have-solutions-problems-two-party-system-cant-solve?__s=dbm6j6fzp8msbjcg2gyq|title=Libertarian Candidate for Gov: I have Solutions to Problems that Two Party System Can't Solve|publisher=[[WAER]]|date=February 19, 2018|accessdate=February 20, 2018}}</ref> Sharpe has advocated for raising revenue for New York by selling naming rights to bridges and highways.<ref name=\"Binghamton\">{{cite web|url=http://www.binghamtonhomepage.com/news/local-news/larry-sharpe-expected-to-receive-libertarian-party-endorsement-for-governor/1063155982|title=Larry Sharpe expected to receive Libertarian Party endorsement for Governor|website=Binghamton Homepage|date=March 20, 2018|accessdate=March 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Abortion===\nSharpe considers himself \"[[pro-choice]]\" as well as \"anti-abortion\". While running for Governor, he vowed to reduce the number of abortions in New York state by increasing availability of other options instead of establishing regulations on abortion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wxxinews.org/post/connections-gubernatorial-candidate-larry-sharpe|title=Coming up on Connections: Friday, September 14|author1=Mack, Megan|author2=Dawson, Evan|date=September 14, 2018|accessdate=September 14, 2018|work=WXXI News}}</ref>\n\n===Criminal justice===\nSharpe favors [[marijuana legalization]], calling for [[hemp]] and marijuana to be \"regulated like onions\".<ref name=Ithaca>{{cite web|url=https://www.ithaca.com/news/libertarian-candidate-for-governor-larry-sharpe-visits-tompkins-county/article_bbc751b8-8116-11e8-931a-9b912d3a9938.html|title=Libertarian candidate for Governor Larry Sharpe visits Tompkins County|author=Reynolds, Nick|date=July 6, 2018|accessdate=August 14, 2018|work=Ithaca.com}}</ref> Sharpe has said he would [[pardon]] those convicted of [[victimless crime]]s or otherwise non-violent offenses.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.waer.org/post/libertarian-candidate-gov-i-have-solutions-problems-two-party-system-cant-solve|title=Libertarian Candidate for Gov: I have Solutions to Problems that Two Party System Can't Solve|author1=Willis, Scott|author2=McMonagle, Liam|author3=Bolt, Chris|date=February 19, 2018|accessdate=August 25, 2018|work=WAER 88.3}}</ref>\n\n===Economy===\nSharpe has supported [[deregulation]] to stimulate economic growth, ending the funding of enforcement of unnecessary regulations. In particular, Sharpe has cited [[occupational licensing]] as a hurdle to small business, describing mandatory licensing for jobs such as barbers and dog walkers as \"barriers to entry and a tax on the poor.\"<ref name= paternalgovt/> Additionally, to reduce the state deficit, Sharpe has called for eliminating [[unfunded mandates]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wktv.com/content/news/Larry-Sharpe-Makes-a-Stop-in-Little-Falls-490677711.html|title=Larry Sharpe Makes a Stop in Little Falls|author=Mooney, Cody|date=August 12, 2018|accessdate=August 14, 2018|publisher=[[WKTV]]}}</ref> He has vowed to follow this reduction in state spending with a reduction in [[property taxes]] and the ultimate repeal of the New York state [[income tax]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thelcn.com/lcn01/governor-candidate-larry-sharpe-shares-appeal-in-area-visit-20180508|title=Governor candidate Larry Sharpe shares appeal in area visit|author=Kendrick, Jim|date=May 8, 2018|accessdate=August 14, 2018|work=Livingston County News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://auburnpub.com/blogs/eye_on_ny/eye-on-ny-larry-sharpe-libertarian-candidate-for-ny-governor/article_616f4e48-719c-11e8-8ca0-2f09abba22f8.html|title=Eye on NY: Larry Sharpe, Libertarian candidate for NY governor, brings message to Auburn|date=June 17, 2018|accessdate=August 14, 2018|author=Harding, Robert|work=auburnpub.com}}</ref>\n\n===Education===\nSharpe has called for the [[decentralization]] of education in New York State and has proposed a \"K-10\" model, reducing the span of high school to ready students for the workforce and/or college.<ref name=Ithaca /><ref name=LTT>{{cite web|url=https://www.saratogatodaynewspaper.com/today-in-saratoga/education/item/8929-let-teachers-teach-with-new-york-state-governor-candidate-larry-sharpe|title=Let Teachers Teach with New York State Governor Candidate Larry Sharpe|date=August 23, 2018|accessdate=August 25, 2018|author=Mahan, Lori|work=Saratoga Today}}</ref> Sharpe has also rejected [[standardized testing]] until high school.<ref name=LTT /> He stated, \"everyone should be able to opt out of testing at any time....it puts kids who have [[special needs]] at a huge disadvantage. Kids who do not test well are labeled as dumb.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Three-more-gubernatorial-candidates-to-watch-12875753.php|title=3 third-party candidates for governor to watch|author=Silberstein, Rachel|date=May 2, 2018|accessdate=August 18, 2018|work=Albany Times Union}}</ref>\n\nAdditionally, Sharpe stated he would refuse [[Categorical grant|federal grants]] for education. He would also abolish the [[Governing boards of colleges and universities in the United States#Regents|Board of Regents]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.syracuse.com/politics/index.ssf/2018/09/staples_bridge_libertarian_gov_candidate_says_lets_lease_naming_rights_on_state.html|title=Legal weed and decentralized education: Can a Libertarian win NY's gov race?|author=Baker, Chris|date=September 17, 2018|accessdate=September 17, 2018|work=Syracuse.com}}</ref>\n\n===Gun laws===\nSharpe vowed, if elected, to repeal the [[NY SAFE Act]] by 2020 and pardon those convicted under its provisions.<ref name= paternalgovt>{{cite web|url=http://www.adirondackdailyenterprise.com/news/local-news/2018/07/sharpe-seeks-a-less-paternal-government/|title=Sharpe seeks a less paternal government|author=Crowley, Peter|date=July 7, 2018|accessdate=August 14, 2018|work=Adirondack Daily Enterprise}}</ref> Sharpe supports allowing school teachers and staff to carry firearms on school grounds, on a voluntary basis.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oswegocountynewsnow.com/news/ny-gov-long-shot-larry-sharpe-visits-oswego/article_feeef2dc-6e7b-11e8-ba2e-c7e21490836f.html|title=NY Gov long shot Larry Sharpe visits Oswego|author=Wallace, Lexie|date=June 13, 2018|accessdate=August 14, 2018|work=Oswego County News Now}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nSharpe lives with his wife Georgia and their two children in [[Queens]], New York.<ref name=\"Meet Larry\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Sharpe mounts campaign to challenge Cuomo |url=http://www.troyrecord.com/article/TR/20180113/NEWS/180119901 |accessdate=August 10, 2018 }}</ref>\n\n==Contributions==\n* {{cite book|title=Igniting Liberty: Voices for Freedom Around the World|isbn=978-1793165039|author1=Barsouk, Adam|author2=Van Staden, Martin|others= Sharpe, Larry (foreword)|year=2019}}\n\n==Electoral history==\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title=New York gubernatorial election, 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nyenr.elections.ny.gov/|title=New York State Unofficial Election Night Results|accessdate=November 7, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181120174014/https://nyenr.elections.ny.gov/|archive-date=November 20, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n  |party      = Democratic Party (United States)\n  |candidate  = ''Andrew Cuomo''\n  |votes      = 3,158,459\n  |percentage = 54.53\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n  |party      = Working Families Party\n  |candidate  = ''Andrew Cuomo''\n  |votes      = 106,008\n  |percentage = 1.83\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n  |party      = Independence Party of New York\